[update:230224] LOFI V2pre

version 2 pre-release. This is a pre-release version, not just the merge model, it also includes some model parts that I have fine-tuned through training, including the previously released TAF and some other train models that improve image quality

But it may cause the model to focus on â€œportrait of charactersâ€, so this is only a pre-release version and needs to be updated. LOFI model aims to be general and high-quality.

Prompt suggestions

  • Since the text-encoder used is enough trained version, do not use a very high attention to control weight, which will cause some wrong drawing, it is recommended that all attention weights be no higher than 1.2

  • If there is no special composition requirement, there is no need for a lot of negative prompts, such as "missing hands", which may affect human body drawing, and DeepNegativeis enough for negative prompts

  • It is strongly recommended to use hires.fix to generate, Recommended parameters:

    • (final output 512*768)

      Steps: 20, Sampler: Euler a, CFG scale: 7, Size: 256x384, Denoising strength: 0.75, Hires upscale: 2, Hires steps: 40, Hires upscaler: Latent (bicubic antialiased)

Most of the sample images are generated with hires.fix

Note: that if you use hires.fix, you may not be able to reproduce the image with the same set of parameters in webui, because hires.fix introduces double randomness

IronCatFateToon

Ñ„Ğ°Ğ¹Ğ» Ğ½Ğ° civitaiÑÑ‚Ñ€Ğ°Ğ½Ğ¸Ñ†Ğ° Ğ½Ğ° civitai

IronCatFateToon

Making models is a thing I do for fun. So if you like what I do? You can help me out by just using the model and leaving a review!

IronCatFateToon's goal is to be able to create nice looking anime style images with vibrant colours, more simplistic anime (cartoony) style look and with influence of Fate/Stay Night: Unlimited Blade Works styling.

In order to achieve what's just been promised I used MeinaMixas the base checkpoint, I then merged two of my style LoRA's into MeinaMix; Anime Vibrancy & Simplify Style (Merge ratio of 0.4`) & Fate/stay night: UBW Style (Merge ratio of 0.6`) . And finally I merged the result of that with the checkpoint Mistoon_Anime. Where I did a weighted merge, 70% was used from the results of me merging the LoRA's into MeinaMix. And 30% was used for Mistoon_Anime. (Note:I didn't use the exact same Anime vibrancy & simplifier Style LoRA when merging, I retrained on the same dataset from that LoRA for a more nuanced look that complimented MeinaMix better i.m.o.)

Some things you might recognize from Fate/stay night: UBW in this checkpoint, is in the way how eyes, scenery, city, cityscape, sky, grass, trees, certain 2.5D angles et cetera are generated. The anime/cartoony look is a combination from my Anime vibrancy & simplifier Style LoRA and Mistoon_Anime. While MeinaMix as a base gives in my own opinion a really sollid base for good looking art.

I haven't used any embeddings in the example images so you should get a good idea, in what the checkpoint can create on its own. I generated the images using some wildcard libraries, so the prompts might sometimes seem random.

Advice:

  • I would recommended a clip skip of 2

  • This checkpoint requires a VAE, I recommend kl-f8-anime2, I've also used it for the examples.

  • I personally like lollypopas an upscaler a lot, it gives anime images a nice soft upscaled touch.

  • I am personally a fan of using DPM++ SDE Karras with 15 steps and when Hires fixing, I like to use 10 for Hires steps and a denoise of about 0.35 or 0.4. Example images had 512x768 as base resolution.

This model wouldn't have been possible without these awesome creators:

  • Mean for MeinaMix

  • Inzania for Mistoon_Anime

SR-Omega v1.0

Ñ„Ğ°Ğ¹Ğ» Ğ½Ğ° civitaiÑÑ‚Ñ€Ğ°Ğ½Ğ¸Ñ†Ğ° Ğ½Ğ° civitai

SR-Omega is a merge of a few handpicked checkpoints/mixes which aims to help generate semi-realistic images.

This was supposed to be an update to SR-Alpha, but the style of this merge's outputs was way too different to be classified as such, as, in my opinion, the images generated with this merge have drastically more realistic proportions compared to the older model.

I highly recommend inpainting for best results and to unlock the full potential of the merge. Separate inpainting model not required. Face restore (GFPGAN) has been used to just bring out a bit of realism to the outputs. I have not tested using Codeformer as it doesn't seem to work on my current set-up (3050 - 4GB VRAM). This does not have a significant impact when inpainting is integral to the workflow, but it does allow for better outputs from raw txt2img, though your mileage may vary.

Recommended Settings:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras (txt2img), or Euler A (inpainting)

  • Sampling Steps: 30

  • CFG = 10

  • Denoising Strength = 0.3-0.5 (img2img/inpainting)

*I only use denoising strength values greater than 0.4 if I want to drastically change the appearance of a particular feature/region of the image. I mainly use this if I want to fix hands that seem to be too deformed to be saved with lower denoising strength values.

Suggested Embeddings:

  • https://civitai.com/models/17083/bad-picture-negative-embedding-for-chilloutmix

  • https://civitai.com/models/11772/verybadimagenegative

  • https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1032948846197747731/1069660323709190195/bad-hands-5.pt

*Orangemix VAE baked in

Credits to the respective original creators of the resources used.

Lunar Diffusion 1.26

This is the first public release of mooncryptowow's Lunar Diffusion model. This model is a high quality blend based off 1.5 and was lovingly crafted to create the most detailed images possible while retaining a large degree of creativity in the renders.

For best results render your images at sizes higher than 512x512. All preview images were created at 576x704 x 2x Swin2sr hires fix with extremely simple prompts on a locked seed (no cherry picking).

Model contains a baked "vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-recommended"

Check me out on Instagram at: https://www.instagram.com/mooncryptowow/
Facebook at: https://www.facebook.com/profile.phpid=100087374733528

I also have a Patreon at https://www.patreon.com/mooncryptowow where I share all of my prompts and settings, uncensored art, custom models and files, as well as general knowledge and tutorials.

Falkons

Ñ„Ğ°Ğ¹Ğ» Ğ½Ğ° civitaiÑÑ‚Ñ€Ğ°Ğ½Ğ¸Ñ†Ğ° Ğ½Ğ° civitai

Introduction

In the world of anime, style and aesthetics play a huge role in creating memorable and captivating characters. From bold and vibrant colors to intricate and detailed designs, there's no limit to the creativity that can be expressed through anime. In this model, we embrace the anime style and bring it to life with our own unique spin. Each character is carefully crafted to embody the essence of the anime universe, with exaggerated features and dynamic poses that capture the imagination. So if you're looking for a model that truly captures the spirit of anime, look no further than our collection.

How to install

  1. Download and install Stable Diffusion, I personally suggest the executable version by AUTOMATIC1111.

  2. Download Falkons model in .safetensor format and insert it into the "ckpt" folder.

  3. Start Stable Diffusion.

  4. Select the "Falkons.safetensor" model from the "Stable Diffusion checkpoint" dropdown menu.

How to use and examples

Of course you can try it with the prompt, sampling methods, steps, CFG, etc. you desire, I use to generate images with:

  • Sampling methods: Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras or DDIM

    • Euler a for a more toon effect

    • DPM++ SDE Karras for an higher realistic effect

    • DDIM for faster generation but higher risk of artifacts and "strange things"

  • Sampling steps: I usually set a minimum of 20 steps, more steps often help to generate a more detailed image, but it's not always true, and typically there is less difference as the number of steps increases.

  • Restore faces, Tiling and Hires. fix turned off

  • Dimensions: I usually pick 640x960, but I have noticed good results with other resolutions such as 512x512, 512x704, 512x960, 624x1176, 720x1024, 1024x1024, while I have experienced poor results with ultrawide resolutions

  • Batch size: my GPU can handle a Batch size of 5, which means 5 images generated per run, it really depends on your GPU's VRAM, so find the highest number you can handle

Here are two examples:

You can start with very easy prompt, such as:

Prompt: a girl,
Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark,
Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 2118282899, Size: 640x960, Model hash: 460b71c1c2, Model: Falkons

Or you can try something more detailed (for example if you want to generate the same character in different poses or in different outfits):

Prompt: masterpiece, best quality, best resolution, girl, nude, perfect anatomy, tight, fantasy worlds background, fantasy, determined, power, flames, intense,night sky, outdoors, moon, stars, clouds, wind, trees, night, sorceress, witch, profession witch, witch uniform, with heels, summoning, glowing runes, neck ribbon, hair ornament, heart jewelry crystal, lace feather white frills, gloves, thighhighs, skirt, thighboots, neckline, extrovert personality, favourite color blue, blue eyes, blue hair, short hair, large breasts, small waist, shiny skin, visible nipples, showing boobs, crotch tattoo, tattoo on underbelly, pussy juice, looking at viewer, magic circle, standing in the center of the circle,

Negative prompt: worst quality, low quality, EasyNegative, comic, sketch, not masterpiece, not best quality, not best resolution, poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, sketches, mutated, mutilated, monochrome, grayscale, greyscale, logo, watermark, duplicate, artifact, noise, film grain, blur, blurry, deformed, distorted, disfigured, fused fingers, extra fingers, twisted, malformed hands, ((((mutated hands and fingers)))), deep depth of field, simple background, abstract background,

Del Toro has long been an inspiration to me since I first saw his 2006 masterpiece "Pans Labyrinth". I've spent countless hours optimising my workflow for this type of full figure checkpoint in dreambooth and I have quite a few models I will now start releasing on a weekly basis.
